claim.claim-text:
18. The method of claim 17, comprising the steps of dissolving albumin in potassium phosphate to form an albumin solution; 
activating methoxy polyethylene glycol with cyanuric chloride and dissolving in water to form a methoxy polyethylene glycol solution; 
adding the methoxy polyethylene glycol solution to the albumin solution to form a mixture; 
stirring the mixture for a suitable time at about room temperature; 
dialyzing the mixture against a phosphate buffered saline solution at about 4° C. for a suitable time, and 
collecting polyethylene glycol modified albumin.
